cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a novel approach for generating house layouts based on a graph constraint, which involves both computer vision (generating bounding boxes) and artificial intelligence (using a GAN). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.AI are the most likely categories. The paper also uses relational architecture, which falls under the category of cs.LG (learning and reasoning with graphs). Additionally, the paper deals with spatial adjacency, which could be categorized under cs.GR (computer graphics) or cs.SI (spatial information).
